svg:text.svg:tspan: To delete a node in a BST, we take the following steps, looking for the to delete and then
carrying out the action based on the situation we find ourselves in:
Begin the deletion process from the root of the BST.
Follow the algorithm from the node search.
Once the node is found, determine its type:
if the node has no left or right child
if the node has exactly one child (either left or right)
if the node has both a left and a right child.
Delete the node based on its type:
Simply remove the node from the tree by setting its parent’s appropriate (left
or right) child pointer to null.
Bypass the node by linking its parent directly to its child. If the node is a left
child, update the parent’s left pointer; if a right child, update the parent’s right pointer.
